%% take your best shot %%

1270
01:04:08,010 --> 01:04:12,079
%% what have you got to lose? %%

1271
01:04:12,081 --> 01:04:14,448
%% Ohh %%

1272
01:04:17,152 --> 01:04:20,021
Dealer:
13. Black's on.

1273
01:04:20,089 --> 01:04:23,257
%% The moment's now %%

1274
01:04:23,325 --> 01:04:25,026
%% don't make me wait %%

1275
01:04:25,060 --> 01:04:26,560
Dealer: Oh, 25.

1276
01:04:29,598 --> 01:04:31,532
Sorry. 23.

1277
01:04:33,201 --> 01:04:35,236
%% And it feels so right %%

1278
01:04:35,304 --> 01:04:37,205
%% it's meant to be %%

1279
01:04:37,272 --> 01:04:38,839
%% it's not about lovin' %%

1280
01:04:38,874 --> 01:04:41,141
%% it's chemistry %%

1281
01:04:41,210 --> 01:04:42,376
Dealer: 6.

1282
01:04:42,444 --> 01:04:44,478
%% Do I have to
spell it out? %%

1283
01:04:44,546 --> 01:04:46,981
%% Baby, read my lips %%

1284
01:04:47,048 --> 01:04:48,282
Dealer:
Place your bets.

1285
01:04:49,951 --> 01:04:52,186
%% What have you
got to lose? %%

1286
01:04:52,253 --> 01:04:54,588
Ella: Ok,
this is it, grandma.

1287
01:04:54,657 --> 01:04:56,824
As they say...

1288
01:04:56,892 --> 01:04:58,759
Here goes nothing.

1289
01:05:03,032 --> 01:05:04,866
Dealer: No more bets.

1290
01:05:04,933 --> 01:05:08,502
%% Ohh, what have you
got to lose? %%

1291
01:05:09,938 --> 01:05:11,605
19!

1292
01:05:11,707 --> 01:05:13,774
Aah! Ha ha ha!
Ha ha ha!

1293
01:05:13,842 --> 01:05:16,710
Ohh, gosh! Aah!

1294
01:05:16,778 --> 01:05:18,913
Ohh! Ohh!

1295
01:05:18,981 --> 01:05:21,415
Ohh! Ohh! Ohh!

1296
01:05:21,483 --> 01:05:24,752
Ok, I am gonna go
get the coin back

1297
01:05:24,819 --> 01:05:26,019
From the pawn shop.

1298
01:05:26,087 --> 01:05:27,721
I'm still feeling lucky.

1299
01:05:27,789 --> 01:05:29,257
Ok.

1300
01:05:29,324 --> 01:05:31,058
Woman: Oh, no!

1301
01:05:40,302 --> 01:05:41,769
Are you ok, ma'am?

1302
01:05:41,836 --> 01:05:44,005
Oh, fine.

1303
01:05:44,072 --> 01:05:46,607
Just a little
excited.

1304
01:05:46,674 --> 01:05:50,111
[Ball rolling]

1305
01:05:50,178 --> 01:05:53,414
Um, last name Gordon.

1306
01:05:53,482 --> 01:05:55,016
First name Douglas.

1307
01:05:55,083 --> 01:05:57,018
<i>Operator:</i>
<i>Hold for that number.</i>

1308
01:05:57,085 --> 01:06:01,755
<i>805-555-0083.</i>

1309
01:06:08,931 --> 01:06:10,464
[Groans]

1310
01:06:10,532 --> 01:06:12,599
[sniffs]

1311
01:06:12,667 --> 01:06:14,902
[cell phone ringing]

1312
01:06:16,171 --> 01:06:17,704
Mom?

1313
01:06:17,773 --> 01:06:20,040
Hi, Richard.
<i>Are you all right?</i>

1314
01:06:20,075 --> 01:06:23,311
We're fine.
We may be in a bit
of trouble, though.

1315
01:06:23,378 --> 01:06:25,078
Don't worry about it.

1316
01:06:25,146 --> 01:06:27,448
I've already been
to that little police
station in Kansas.

1317
01:06:27,515 --> 01:06:28,950
<i>It's been taken care of.</i>

1318
01:06:29,017 --> 01:06:30,351
Thank you.

1319
01:06:30,452 --> 01:06:32,787
Where are you?
Where are <i>you?</i>

1320
01:06:32,854 --> 01:06:34,621
I'm getting closer.

1321
01:06:34,689 --> 01:06:36,223
How are you feeling?

1322
01:06:36,291 --> 01:06:37,557
Oh, I'm fine.

1323
01:06:37,625 --> 01:06:39,293
I just got some more
of my medication.

1324
01:06:39,360 --> 01:06:41,361
<i>You didn't sell</i>
<i>my house, did you?</i>

1325
01:06:41,429 --> 01:06:43,563
Nope. Not yet.

1326
01:06:43,631 --> 01:06:45,332
Why don't you tell me
where you are

1327
01:06:45,400 --> 01:06:47,301
So I can wire you
some money, just in case?

1328
01:06:47,368 --> 01:06:48,836
We don't need money.

1329
01:06:48,904 --> 01:06:51,471
We're not far
from Annie's point.

1330
01:06:51,539 --> 01:06:53,640
I assume you know
where that is.

1331
01:06:53,675 --> 01:06:56,376
Mom--
see you there.

1332
01:06:56,478 --> 01:06:57,744
Mom?

1333
01:06:58,880 --> 01:07:00,347
[Hangs up]

1334
01:07:01,950 --> 01:07:03,750
[chuckles]

1335
01:07:08,356 --> 01:07:10,958
Ella: I know that
you have this trip
perfectly planned out,

1336
01:07:11,026 --> 01:07:13,260
But we're going
on a little detour.

1337
01:07:13,328 --> 01:07:14,896
Annie: The last time
that happened,

1338
01:07:14,963 --> 01:07:17,197
Your father took me to
that retirement village.

1339
01:07:17,265 --> 01:07:18,733
Where are we going?

1340
01:07:18,801 --> 01:07:21,201
There's someone that
I think you should see.

1341
01:07:38,687 --> 01:07:40,621
[Turns engine off]

1342
01:07:45,260 --> 01:07:47,461
That's a nice house.

1343
01:07:47,529 --> 01:07:49,096
It sure is.

1344
01:07:50,465 --> 01:07:53,000
It's your brother's house.

1345
01:08:00,842 --> 01:08:02,543
I can't.

1346
01:08:02,611 --> 01:08:05,879
I'm sure he'll be
happy to see you.

1347
01:08:13,321 --> 01:08:16,356
Did you ever think that
you might owe it to him?

1348
01:08:21,129 --> 01:08:23,431
[Doorbell rings]

1349
01:08:23,498 --> 01:08:25,566
Don't be nervous.

1350
01:08:25,634 --> 01:08:27,968
Oh, that's easy
for you to say.

1351
01:08:32,207 --> 01:08:33,841
May I help you?

1352
01:08:36,812 --> 01:08:38,979
Annie?

1353
01:08:39,081 --> 01:08:41,048
Hi, Dougie.

1354
01:08:43,017 --> 01:08:44,785
This is
my granddaughter.

1355
01:08:44,852 --> 01:08:47,621
I guess she'd be
your great-niece Ella.

1356
01:08:47,689 --> 01:08:48,922
Nice to meet you.

1357
01:08:48,990 --> 01:08:51,225
It's really nice
to meet you, too.

1358
01:08:53,495 --> 01:08:54,795
Ohh.

1359
01:08:57,165 --> 01:08:59,600
Uh...
Who's this, dad?

1360
01:08:59,667 --> 01:09:01,736
Well, this is
your aunt Annie,

1361
01:09:01,803 --> 01:09:04,504
And this is your
cousin Ella.

1362
01:09:04,573 --> 01:09:06,673
Annie, Ella...

1363
01:09:06,742 --> 01:09:08,576
This is
my daughter Lucy.

1364
01:09:18,486 --> 01:09:19,887
Thanks for dinner.

1365
01:09:19,955 --> 01:09:22,189
Oh, you're welcome.
It wasn't much.

1366
01:09:24,392 --> 01:09:26,493
Lucy's beautiful.

1367
01:09:26,561 --> 01:09:28,462
She gets that
from her mother.

1368
01:09:28,529 --> 01:09:29,730
I'm sorry she's
out of town.

1369
01:09:29,798 --> 01:09:31,198
She would've loved
to meet you.

1370
01:09:31,265 --> 01:09:33,166
I'm sorry, too.

1371
01:09:38,040 --> 01:09:40,107
Eliot?

1372
01:09:43,011 --> 01:09:45,346
He fought so hard...

1373
01:09:45,380 --> 01:09:47,815
For so long.

1374
01:09:47,882 --> 01:09:50,284
He went peacefully.

1375
01:09:52,387 --> 01:09:54,188
He was a good man.

1376
01:09:56,891 --> 01:09:59,226
Very good man.

1377
01:09:59,294 --> 01:10:01,329
Uh, our son Richard

1378
01:10:01,396 --> 01:10:03,798
Took over Eliot's
construction company.

1379
01:10:03,865 --> 01:10:06,367
Oh, good for him.

1380
01:10:06,435 --> 01:10:08,369
That's good.

1381
01:10:08,437 --> 01:10:12,206
Annie... Heh.

1382
01:10:12,241 --> 01:10:13,807
I picked up the phone

1383
01:10:13,875 --> 01:10:15,376
To call you
a thousand times.

1384
01:10:15,443 --> 01:10:17,545
But, as each year
went by,

1385
01:10:17,612 --> 01:10:19,179
It just got more
and more difficult

1386
01:10:19,247 --> 01:10:21,048
To know
what to say.

1387
01:10:21,116 --> 01:10:23,884
Don't blame yourself.
I have a phone, too.

1388
01:10:23,951 --> 01:10:28,255
I never should've tried
to teach you that lesson.

1389
01:10:28,357 --> 01:10:31,058
And for that I've never
forgiven myself.

1390
01:10:31,125 --> 01:10:33,126
I'd be lying
if I told you

1391
01:10:33,161 --> 01:10:35,062
The price wasn't high
in not seeing you

1392
01:10:35,129 --> 01:10:37,164
And Eliot and Richard.

1393
01:10:37,232 --> 01:10:40,000
But, you know,
it made me
who I am today.

1394
01:10:40,068 --> 01:10:41,669
I work with kids,

1395
01:10:41,736 --> 01:10:43,937
Trying to help them
find direction
in their lives,

1396
01:10:44,005 --> 01:10:47,541
And I never would've
been able to do that
without you, Annie.

1397
01:10:47,609 --> 01:10:50,911
I never doubted
you'd make a success
of yourself, Doug.

1398
01:10:54,682 --> 01:10:57,018
I miss you.

1399
01:10:58,686 --> 01:11:00,687
Miss you, too.

1400
01:11:04,292 --> 01:11:05,893
[Laughing]

1401
01:11:05,960 --> 01:11:07,594
So, what happened
with the cop?

1402
01:11:07,662 --> 01:11:09,497
Nothing.
My dad met with him,

1403
01:11:09,564 --> 01:11:11,332
And he dropped
all the charges.

1404
01:11:11,400 --> 01:11:12,966
He was so embarrassed

1405
01:11:13,035 --> 01:11:14,835
That an older woman locked
him in his own cell.

1406
01:11:14,903 --> 01:11:17,038
He's not gonna tell
anybody anything.

1407
01:11:17,105 --> 01:11:19,840
So, how long have you
and aunt Annie been driving?

1408
01:11:19,908 --> 01:11:22,276
About three days.

1409
01:11:22,344 --> 01:11:24,311
Who would think
it'd be fun to drive
across country

1410
01:11:24,379 --> 01:11:26,313
With their grandma?

1411
01:11:26,381 --> 01:11:29,250
I gotta tell you,
when she and I first
got in the car...

1412
01:11:29,317 --> 01:11:31,352
I would've rather
been anywhere else.

1413
01:11:31,420 --> 01:11:34,055
I mean, I never thought
that my grandma

1414
01:11:34,122 --> 01:11:36,123
Could understand
anything

1415
01:11:36,191 --> 01:11:38,426
That was going on
in my world.

1416
01:11:38,460 --> 01:11:40,327
And?

1417
01:11:40,395 --> 01:11:42,196
She taught me more
in a few days

1418
01:11:42,264 --> 01:11:44,631
Than I ever would've
learned in school.

1419
01:11:44,699 --> 01:11:46,300
You're in college?

1420
01:11:46,368 --> 01:11:47,601
I was.

1421
01:11:47,668 --> 01:11:48,969
Well, what happened?

1422
01:11:49,037 --> 01:11:50,905
I left.

1423
01:11:50,972 --> 01:11:53,473
So, you just quit?

1424
01:11:53,541 --> 01:11:57,211
Well, my music never
would've had a Chance
if I didn't.

1425
01:11:59,180 --> 01:12:01,282
What do <i>you</i>
want to be?

1426
01:12:01,350 --> 01:12:03,150
A writer.

1427
01:12:03,185 --> 01:12:04,952
That's awesome.

1428
01:12:05,019 --> 01:12:07,654
It would be awesome
to actually have
a book published.

1429
01:12:07,722 --> 01:12:10,324
A wise woman
once told me

1430
01:12:10,391 --> 01:12:14,060
That the world is open
to all of our dreams.

1431
01:12:14,129 --> 01:12:16,497
And what if they're
just dreams?

1432
01:12:16,564 --> 01:12:19,099
Well, you won't know
until you try.

1433
01:12:19,134 --> 01:12:21,468
You gotta do
what makes you happy.

1434
01:12:28,577 --> 01:12:30,444
[Grunts]

1435
01:12:50,265 --> 01:12:52,032
Here's some
water, Annie.

1436
01:12:52,100 --> 01:12:53,567
Oh.

1437
01:12:57,539 --> 01:12:59,006
Thank you.

1438
01:12:59,073 --> 01:13:00,441
Those are
some big pills.

1439
01:13:00,509 --> 01:13:02,976
What are those for?

1440
01:13:03,044 --> 01:13:05,513
I'm just getting old.
[Chuckles]

1441
01:13:05,580 --> 01:13:07,447
Are you all right?
Oh, I'm fine.

1442
01:13:07,516 --> 01:13:09,884
It's been
a long Journey.

1443
01:13:09,951 --> 01:13:11,552
Nothing a good
night's sleep

1444
01:13:11,620 --> 01:13:14,521
And comfortable bed
won't fix. Ha ha!

1445
01:13:14,589 --> 01:13:17,391
Oh, it's really good
to see you, Doug.

1446
01:13:17,459 --> 01:13:18,758
Same here.

1447
01:13:18,826 --> 01:13:20,560
Now, you're sure
you're all right?

1448
01:13:20,628 --> 01:13:21,862
Oh, I'm fine.

1449
01:13:21,930 --> 01:13:23,464
'Cause I'm right next door
if you need me.

1450
01:13:23,531 --> 01:13:25,366
Fine.

1451
01:13:27,135 --> 01:13:28,768
Good night, Annie.

1452
01:13:38,613 --> 01:13:40,046
You need
anything else?

1453
01:13:40,114 --> 01:13:42,883
Oh, we're fine,
thank you.

1454
01:13:42,950 --> 01:13:44,284
Well...

1455
01:13:46,621 --> 01:13:48,856
Bye, Annie.

1456
01:13:48,923 --> 01:13:51,859
So, let's not let
another 30 years
go by, ok?

1457
01:13:51,926 --> 01:13:54,795
Ok. I'll talk
to you soon.

1458
01:13:59,133 --> 01:14:01,502
Wait, Annie.

1459
01:14:05,072 --> 01:14:06,940
I just--
I wish so much

1460
01:14:07,008 --> 01:14:10,110
That I could've talked
to Eliot one last time.

1461
01:14:10,177 --> 01:14:12,245
I'm so sorry I didn't.

1462
01:14:12,347 --> 01:14:15,048
But mostly,
I'm sorry that...

1463
01:14:15,116 --> 01:14:17,117
I wasn't there for you.

1464
01:14:17,184 --> 01:14:20,354
So, even if we
haven't spoken,

1465
01:14:20,421 --> 01:14:23,257
You were always
there with me.

1466
01:14:23,324 --> 01:14:24,758
Thank you.

1467
01:14:24,825 --> 01:14:26,360
Hey.

1468
01:14:26,427 --> 01:14:28,395
Happy 50th anniversary.

1469
01:14:28,463 --> 01:14:30,163
Thank you.

1470
01:14:33,635 --> 01:14:35,101
Have a nice trip.

1471
01:14:35,203 --> 01:14:37,237
Come back, ok?
Thank you.

1472
01:14:38,372 --> 01:14:39,873
I'm proud of you, Doug.

1473
01:14:39,941 --> 01:14:41,775
Eliot would be, too.

1474
01:14:53,722 --> 01:14:55,455
[Door closes]

1475
01:14:58,492 --> 01:15:00,260
[engine starts]

1476
01:15:22,583 --> 01:15:24,651
[sighs]

1477
01:15:26,587 --> 01:15:28,989
Grandma, I think
we need to get you out
of this car for a while.

1478
01:15:29,057 --> 01:15:30,190
No.

1479
01:15:30,258 --> 01:15:32,492
But you look really
uncomfortable.

1480
01:15:32,560 --> 01:15:34,494
Ella bear,
in less than two hours,

1481
01:15:34,562 --> 01:15:37,531
I'll have more energy
than I'll know what
to do with.

1482
01:15:37,598 --> 01:15:39,166
Trust me.

1483
01:16:05,760 --> 01:16:07,427
Hey.

1484
01:16:16,771 --> 01:16:19,373
Annie: It's more beautiful
than I remember.

1485
01:16:24,945 --> 01:16:28,248
It hasn't changed
one bit.

1486
01:16:31,653 --> 01:16:34,488
It's as though we were
here yesterday.

1487
01:16:36,057 --> 01:16:39,426
Oh, your grandfather
looked so handsome.

1488
01:17:39,153 --> 01:17:41,989
I'm ready to take
grandpa home now.

1489
01:17:45,593 --> 01:17:47,127
Richard: Brenda?
<i>Yes?</i>

1490
01:17:47,195 --> 01:17:48,628
You got the three
wise men on the phone?

1491
01:17:48,696 --> 01:17:49,930
<i>Uh-huh.</i>
Great.

1492
01:17:49,998 --> 01:17:51,131
Put 'em through.

1493
01:17:51,199 --> 01:17:52,632
<i>Ok.</i>

1494
01:17:55,069 --> 01:17:56,469
Gentlemen.
<i>Hello, Richard.</i>

1495
01:17:56,537 --> 01:17:57,805
Are we all together?

1496
01:17:57,872 --> 01:17:59,173
<i>Yes, we're all here.</i>
Good.

1497
01:17:59,240 --> 01:18:00,640
<i>Listen, we'd like to</i>
<i>talk to you about--</i>

1498
01:18:00,708 --> 01:18:02,109
Let me start out
by saying that,

1499
01:18:02,177 --> 01:18:03,944
While I can certainly
appreciate your desire

1500
01:18:04,012 --> 01:18:05,979
To see these projects
through to completion,

1501
01:18:06,047 --> 01:18:08,282
What I do not appreciate
is being talked to

1502
01:18:08,349 --> 01:18:09,950
And treated
like an amateur.

1503
01:18:10,018 --> 01:18:12,352
My father put all
three of you on the map,
and your companies,

1504
01:18:12,420 --> 01:18:14,654
Without ever
letting you down,
and I won't, either.

1505
01:18:14,722 --> 01:18:16,824
But right now
my family needs me,

1506
01:18:16,891 --> 01:18:18,658
And I refuse to
let <i>them</i> down.

1507
01:18:18,726 --> 01:18:20,828
So, I will contact you
when I get back to town,

1508
01:18:20,895 --> 01:18:22,062
And when that happens,

1509
01:18:22,130 --> 01:18:23,897
I will fulfill
all of my obligations,

1510
01:18:23,964 --> 01:18:26,266
As I expect you
to fulfill all of yours.

1511
01:18:26,334 --> 01:18:28,235
We understand each other?
<i>Yes, we do.</i>

1512
01:18:28,303 --> 01:18:31,571
Excellent.
Have a nice day.

1513
01:18:54,763 --> 01:18:57,296
Are you sure
this is it?

1514
01:18:57,364 --> 01:18:59,633
I'm sure. Heh!

1515
01:19:20,388 --> 01:19:22,055
Is it how
you remembered?

1516
01:19:22,123 --> 01:19:24,658
It's beautiful.

1517
01:19:35,269 --> 01:19:38,204
Well, now I can see what
the fuss was all about.

1518
01:19:40,107 --> 01:19:42,942
Hey.
Oh!

1519
01:19:45,313 --> 01:19:47,180
Hi, daddy.
Hi, honey.

1520
01:19:48,816 --> 01:19:50,750
Annie:
Thank you, Richard.

1521
01:19:50,818 --> 01:19:52,819
I'm sorry you thought
you had to chase me

1522
01:19:52,886 --> 01:19:54,521
Clear across country.

1523
01:19:54,589 --> 01:19:58,091
But coming here was
very important to me.

1524
01:19:58,158 --> 01:19:59,926
When I started
this Journey,

1525
01:19:59,993 --> 01:20:03,129
I honestly believed
I'd soon be joining
your father.

1526
01:20:03,197 --> 01:20:05,765
I guess what I'm
trying to say is...

1527
01:20:05,833 --> 01:20:07,934
I'm sorry I made life
so difficult.

1528
01:20:07,969 --> 01:20:08,935
You were just
looking for support.

1529
01:20:09,003 --> 01:20:10,470
No, I was being selfish.

1530
01:20:10,537 --> 01:20:13,606
You were the one doing
your best to help.

1531
01:20:16,010 --> 01:20:17,710
But now that I'm here,

1532
01:20:17,779 --> 01:20:21,248
I feel reborn.

1533
01:20:21,315 --> 01:20:23,183
And I owe a lot
of that to Ella.

1534
01:20:23,284 --> 01:20:24,484
Ohh.

1535
01:20:24,552 --> 01:20:26,886
She's just like
her mother.

1536
01:20:26,954 --> 01:20:30,389
Well, and she's also
just like her father.

1537
01:20:30,458 --> 01:20:32,392
You're a good dad,
Richard.

1538
01:20:34,962 --> 01:20:37,130
Your father would be
proud of you.

1539
01:21:02,289 --> 01:21:03,790
Wow.

1540
01:21:05,627 --> 01:21:08,862
Yeah. Dad told me
about this.

1541
01:21:08,929 --> 01:21:10,464
He wanted you
to have it.

1542
01:21:11,732 --> 01:21:13,700
Thanks.

1543
01:21:18,906 --> 01:21:21,174
I'll only be a minute.

1544
01:21:35,990 --> 01:21:38,624
[Sighs]

1545
01:21:38,693 --> 01:21:42,062
Oh, Eliot, we made it!

1546
01:21:42,130 --> 01:21:44,231
And on time!

1547
01:21:45,933 --> 01:21:48,334
Wasn't able to finish
the picture, Eliot.

1548
01:21:48,402 --> 01:21:52,438
I was afraid
I forgot what
the place looks like.

1549
01:21:52,507 --> 01:21:54,374
But it's the same,
isn't it?

1550
01:22:00,682 --> 01:22:02,015
[Laughs] ohh!

1551
01:22:02,083 --> 01:22:05,018
Oh, I miss you,
my dear.

1552
01:22:05,086 --> 01:22:07,654
You could always
make me laugh.

1553
01:22:11,292 --> 01:22:14,061
I heard you sing.

1554
01:22:14,128 --> 01:22:16,329
I know.

1555
01:22:16,397 --> 01:22:18,831
You were really,
really good.

1556
01:22:18,899 --> 01:22:21,568
I wish your mom
could've heard you.

1557
01:22:21,635 --> 01:22:23,370
I think she did.

1558
01:22:25,239 --> 01:22:28,007
I miss her so much.

1559
01:22:28,076 --> 01:22:29,842
I've never been able
to let her go.

1560
01:22:29,910 --> 01:22:33,113
But that's no excuse
for me to be as hard
on you as I've been.

1561
01:22:33,181 --> 01:22:35,848
You're just
being a dad.
Yeah.

1562
01:22:35,917 --> 01:22:38,618
And, as your dad,

1563
01:22:38,685 --> 01:22:41,320
I need to
tell you that...

1564
01:22:41,388 --> 01:22:43,389
You don't have to go
back to school.

1565
01:22:46,127 --> 01:22:48,728
I just need something
else right now.

1566
01:22:50,765 --> 01:22:54,000
But I promise I won't
leave you in the dark
anymore.

1567
01:22:54,068 --> 01:22:56,269
I'll let you know
what I'm feeling...

1568
01:22:56,336 --> 01:22:58,304
Whether you like it
or not.

1569
01:22:58,406 --> 01:23:00,273
[Laughs] ok.

1570
01:23:02,009 --> 01:23:03,676
Let's go see how
your grandma's doing.

1571
01:23:10,785 --> 01:23:13,519
Mom? You ok?

1572
01:23:17,258 --> 01:23:19,125
Mom?

1573
01:23:19,193 --> 01:23:20,994
Grandma!
Mom!

1574
01:23:21,062 --> 01:23:22,728
Are you ok?

1575
01:23:22,797 --> 01:23:27,066
Can't an old woman
take a nap without a fuss?

1576
01:23:27,135 --> 01:23:29,135
Ohh, for a minute
there, I, uh...

1577
01:23:29,203 --> 01:23:30,403
Thought maybe...

1578
01:23:30,471 --> 01:23:32,439
You thought what?
Well--

1579
01:23:32,440 --> 01:23:34,841
That I came
all this way to die?

1580
01:23:34,908 --> 01:23:36,409
Are you kidding me?

1581
01:23:36,477 --> 01:23:38,311
Did you take
your medication?

1582
01:23:38,379 --> 01:23:41,714
What do I tell you
every time you ask?
Sorry.

1583
01:23:41,782 --> 01:23:44,317
You can be
a bit of a pest.

1584
01:23:44,352 --> 01:23:46,953
But I know
you mean well.

1585
01:23:57,665 --> 01:23:59,198
Shall we?

1586
01:24:22,356 --> 01:24:24,557
Happy anniversary, my love.

1587
01:24:26,527 --> 01:24:28,995
[Seagulls squawking]

1588
01:27:08,007 --> 01:27:09,995
---the end---
